  "chapter": {
    "number": 47,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Judgment on the Philistines"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "This is the word of the LORD that came to Jeremiah the prophet about the Philistines before Pharaoh struck down Gaza."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "This is what the LORD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“See how the waters are rising from the north",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and becoming an overflowing torrent.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They will overflow the land and its fullness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the cities and their inhabitants.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The people will cry out,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and all who dwell in the land will wail",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "at the sound of the galloping hooves of stallions,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the rumbling of chariots,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and the clatter of their wheels.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The fathers will not turn back for their sons;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their hands will hang limp.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the day has come",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to destroy all the Philistines,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to cut off from Tyre and Sidon",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "every remaining ally.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Indeed, the LORD is about to destroy the Philistines,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the remnant from the coasts of Caphtor.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2987
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The people of Gaza will shave their heads in mourning;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Ashkelon will be silenced.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "O remnant of their valley,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2988
          },
          {
            "text": "how long will you gash yourself?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "‘Alas, O sword of the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "how long until you rest?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Return to your sheath;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "cease and be still!’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "How can it rest",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when the LORD has commanded it?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He has appointed it against Ashkelon",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the shore of its coastland.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 2987,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "That is, Crete",
